

 what 'JS' can do on HTML page in browser-envi?
 
 
  JS using Web APIs can bring any dynamic-behav to HTML-pag in browser.
  
  what Web APIs ?
  
   e.g
   
      DOM , XHR ( AJAX ) , Timer 
      
      HTML-5 --> canvas , audio/video , WebGL , Geo , localStorage
      
      some Web APIs are based on 'w3c' standard.
      
      
    using DOM API
    
    --> cat create/retreive/update/delete HTML elements.
    --> can change element's style
    --> can change element's attribute values
    --> can change element's text content
    --> can validate form-fields
    --> can create rich UI components
    --> can listen/handle events
    
    using XHR API
    
    --> can communicate with server-side programs , update results
        in existing page ( AJAX )
    
    using TimerAPI
    
